The numbers are placed on a square spiral  

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
\cdots &5&4&3\cdots\\
\cdots &6&1&2\cdots\\
\cdots &7&8&9\cdots
\end{array}
\]

which goes  

right → up → left → down, repeating with side‑lengths \(1,1,2,2,3,3,\dots\).

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1.  Coordinates of the numbers  

Put the centre \(1\) at \((0,0)\).  
For any integer \(k\ge 0\) the numbers of the outer “ring’’ (layer) \(k\) satisfy  

\[
k=\max\{|x|,|y|\},\qquad 
m_k=(2k+1)^2 \text{ at }(k,-k)
\]

and the first number of this layer is  

\[
s_k=(2k-1)^2+1 =4k^{2}-4k+2
\]

situated at \((k,\;-(k-1))\).

If a point \((x,y)\) lies on that ring, its offset from \(s_k\) is

\[
\begin{cases}
\displaystyle y-[-(k-1)], & x=k \quad(\text{right side})\\[4pt]
\displaystyle 2k+(k-1-x), & y=k \quad(\text{top side})\\[4pt]
\displaystyle 4k+(k-1-y), & x=-k \quad(\text{left side})\\[4pt]
\displaystyle 6k+(x+k-1), & y=-k \quad(\text{bottom side})
\end{cases}
\]

and the number is \(N(x,y)=s_k+\) offset.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2.  Position of 2026  

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx45.0,\qquad
k=\Bigl\lceil\frac{\sqrt{2026}-1}{2}\Bigr\rceil =23 .
\]

Thus 2026 is the first element of layer 23,
\[
2026 = s_{23}\quad\text{at}\quad (23,-22).
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 3.  The eight neighbours  

The eight surrounding coordinates are  

\[
\begin{aligned}
&(22,-23),\;(23,-23),\;(24,-23),\\
&(22,-22),\;(24,-22),\\
&(22,-21),\;(23,-21),\;(24,-21).
\end{aligned}
\]

Applying the formula above:

| \((x,y)\) | layer \(k\) | side | number |
|-----------|------------|------|--------|
| (22,-23) | 23 | bottom | \(2026+182 = 2208\) |
| (23,-23) | 23 | bottom | \(2026+183 = 2209\) |
| (24,-23) | 24 | right (start) | \(2210\) |
| (22,-22) | 22 | bottom (max) | \(2025\) |
| (24,-22) | 24 | right | \(2210+1 = 2211\) |
| (22,-21) | 22 | right (start) | \(1850\) |
| (23,-21) | 23 | right | \(2026+1 = 2027\) |
| (24,-21) | 24 | right | \(2210+2 = 2212\) |

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 4.  Sum of the neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\Sigma &=2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212\\
       &=16952.
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
----
